  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "Fixes the flake in `TestSendMessageWithModelOverrideUpdatesLastModelConfigID` (and the same pattern in `TestSubsequentSendWithoutOverrideUsesPersistedModel`).\n\n## Root Cause\n\nBoth tests assert `require.Len(t, messages, 1)` immediately after a direct-send `CreateChatMessage`. The background chat daemon can process the message and insert an assistant response before the assertion runs, resulting in 2 messages instead of 1.\n\n## Fix\n\nReplace the strict count assertion with `slices.IndexFunc` to find the user message by role, then verify its `ModelConfigID`. The test's actual purpose is verifying model override persistence, not message count.\n\nFixes: ENG-2719\n\n> Generated with [Coder Agents](https://coder.com/agents)",
